\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The area being optimized is usually divided in squares (or pixels) of a
 certain size, which may vary from 10 to 100 meters, creating a grid of
 a certain resolution.
 A square is considered covered, if the signal to noise ratio is above a
 given threshold 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
